Description: Setting up your AWS IAM Credentials

In order to connect to an AWS EKS Service, you will need to setup
your AWS IAM Credentials to autnticiate.

To setup your AWS IAM Creditals using the aws cli tool you will
will need you AWS Access Key ID and Secrete Access Key.

  aws configure --profile {aws-iam-user}

Example:
  > aws configure --profile johnsmith
  AWS Access Key ID [None]: ABCD1234EFJK5678
  AWS Secret Access Key [None]: abcd1234efjk5678lmno90
  Default region name [None]:
  Default output format [None]: